Sunnahs Regarding The Bathroom/toilet:

To Enter The Bathroom/toilet With Your Head Covered.

To Enter The Bathroom/toilet Wearing Footwear.

To Recite The Dua On Entering The Bathroom/toilet:- اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَعُوذُ بِكَ مِنَ الْخُبُثِ وَالْخَبَائِثِ

To Enter With The Left Foot.
To Sit/squat And Urinate.
One Should Never Urinate Whilst Standing If Avoidable.

One Should Not Face Or Show His Back Towards The Qiblah.
To Not Speak Whilst In The Bathroom/toilet.

To Be Mindful Of Splashes Of Urine. (Being Unmindful Can Cause One To Be Punished In The Grave
To Clean Oneself With Water After Relieving Oneself.

To Leave The Bathroom/toilet With The Right Foot.

To Recite The Dua After Leaving The Bathroom/toilet:- غُفْرَانَكَ And الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ الَّذِي أَذْهَبَ عَنِّي الأَذَى وَعَافَانِي
